<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="120" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,258,895]" box="[151,458,258,283]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,244,258,283]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Length.</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity box="[323,454,258,283]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.4">3.4–3.6mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,294,319]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Color.</emphasis>
General color ochraceous (
<figureCitation box="[610,701,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Vertex with dark brown, orange-red or brownish red band interrupted medially. Vertex and pronotum with brown dots (
<figureCitation box="[829,909,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
A). Face with dark brown markings (
<figureCitation box="[1321,1402,330,355]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
C). Pronotum, mesonotum and scutellum with orange-red longitudinal band. Forewing with brown hue (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1358,366,391]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
A).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,402,427]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Body.</emphasis>
Head narrower than pronotum, anterior margin rounded to face, acutely angled. Vertex longer than width between eyes (
<figureCitation box="[388,469,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
A). Ocellus next to eye slightly below anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1093,1175,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
B). Eye relatively large (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
A). Anteclypeus parallel-sided, extending slightly beyond normal curve of genae (
<figureCitation box="[1197,1281,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
C). Pronotum median length slightly shorter than median length of crown. Mesonotum and scutellum shorter than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[159,234,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig.15</figureCitation>
A). Forewing macropterous (
<figureCitation box="[558,639,546,571]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1895,1917]" captionTargetBox="[172,1431,1003,1837]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[158,1443,993,1848]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. Male. A: habitus, dorsal view; B: habitus, lateral view; C: face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255866/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,258,895]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,582,607]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Male.</emphasis>
Pygofer side with few macrosetae dorsally, apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[928,1010,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,204,1670]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[233,1354,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 16. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view (valve is broken); C – D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, dorsal view; G: connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255867/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
A). Subgenital plate rounded laterally, macrosetae uniseriate laterally (
<figureCitation box="[528,618,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,204,1670]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[233,1354,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 16. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view (valve is broken); C – D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, dorsal view; G: connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255867/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
B). Style apophysis digitate, strongly laterally curved (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1367,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,204,1670]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[233,1354,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 16. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view (valve is broken); C – D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, dorsal view; G: connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255867/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
C–D). Connective H-shaped, stem shorter than anterior arms (
<figureCitation box="[788,872,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,204,1670]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[233,1354,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 16. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view (valve is broken); C – D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, dorsal view; G: connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255867/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
E). Aedeagal shaft tapered distally to acute apex, relatively straight and diverging from basal apodeme in lateral view, lower part semi-circular in cross section (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1704,1726]" captionTargetBox="[245,1341,204,1670]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[233,1354,193,1683]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 16. Stirellus multipunctatus sp. nov. A: male pygofer side, lateral view; B: valve and subgenital plate, ventral view (valve is broken); C – D: style, dorsal view; E: connective, dorsal view; F: aedeagus, dorsal view; G: connective and aedeagus, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255867/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
F–G).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
